  "original_title": "\u0b8f\u0bb1\u0bbe\u0bb5\u0bc2\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bae\u0bc1\u0bb1\u0bc8: \u0b9a\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc7\u0b95 \u0ba8\u0baa\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0bb0\u0ba3\u0b9f\u0bc8\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Ebravoor violence: Suspect surrenders",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The main suspect, who was wanted in connection with the violent incident that took place on the night of May 9th in Ebravoor, Batticaloa, surrendered yesterday (26) at the Ebravoor Tourism Magistrate's Court.",
        "After the surrender of the suspect through lawyer Habib Muhammad Riban, the judge Anwar Sadat of the Tourism Magistrate's Court of Ebravur has ordered that he be remanded till September 9.",
        "The prime suspect surrendered yesterday while 38 people had already been arrested and interrogated by the District Crime Investigation Department in connection with the burning and looting of the rented office of the Member of Parliament and Environment Minister Naseer Ahmed, his relative's house and hostels, as well as the destruction of 3 garment factories. (a)"
      ],
